#. <section class="sutta" id="an7.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.38:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.38:0.2"
msgid "4. devatāvagga"
msgstr "4. Deities"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an7.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Paṭhamapaṭisambhidāsutta"
msgstr "38. Textual Analysis (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.33"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an7.38:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Sattahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu nacirasseva catasso "
"paṭisambhidā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant with seven qualities will soon realize the four "
"kinds of textual analysis and live having achieved them with their own "
"insight."

msgctxt "an7.38:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi sattahi?"
msgstr "What seven?"

# See BB’s note.
msgctxt "an7.38:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ me cetaso līnattan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti;"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant truly understands: ‘This is mental sluggishness.’"

msgctxt "an7.38:1.4"
msgid ""
"ajjhattaṃ saṅkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘ajjhattaṃ me saṅkhittaṃ cittan’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti;"
msgstr ""
"They truly understand internally contracted mind as ‘internally contracted "
"mind’."

msgctxt "an7.38:1.5"
msgid ""
"bahiddhā vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘bahiddhā me vikkhittaṃ cittan’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānāti;"
msgstr ""
"They truly understand externally scattered mind as ‘externally scattered "
"mind’."

msgctxt "an7.38:1.6"
msgid ""
"tassa viditā vedanā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchanti;"
msgstr "They know feelings as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away."

msgctxt "an7.38:1.7"
msgid ""
"viditā saññā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti;"
msgstr ""
"They know perceptions as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away."

msgctxt "an7.38:1.8"
msgid ""
"viditā vitakkā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti;"
msgstr "They know thoughts as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away."

msgctxt "an7.38:1.9"
msgid ""
"sappāyāsappāyesu kho panassa dhammesu hīnappaṇītesu kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāgesu "
"nimittaṃ suggahitaṃ hoti sumanasikataṃ sūpadhāritaṃ suppaṭividdhaṃ paññāya."
msgstr ""
"The characteristics of qualities—suitable or unsuitable, inferior or "
"superior, or those on the side of dark or bright—are properly grasped, "
"attended, borne in mind, and comprehended with wisdom."

msgctxt "an7.38:1.10"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, sattahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu nacirasseva "
"catasso paṭisambhidā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with these seven qualities will soon realize the four kinds of "
"textual analysis and live having achieved them with their own insight.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.38:1.11"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
